snippet.textDisplay:
I've always thought that the first comment on YouTube was the most liked, but I've never actually seen it and tracking down specific YouTube comments is a lost cause sometimes other than combing through video comment sections. Also, I'm not even sure what video the first comment is on, but I'll take a guess it's on the first VIDEO on YouTube which is of course "Me at the zoo" (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jNQXAC9IVRw) which has 4,204,541 Comments as of posting this comment (It's currently 1:40 AM MST) and is growing by the minute. The first video on YouTube quite possibly has the most active comment section, but is really because of people spamming for whatever reason.

Good luck finding that comment for whoever wants to scroll to it.
